      • getFormat

        Gets the common RAW string format code of the given range of cells

        see https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/number-format-codes-5026bbd6-04bc-48cd-bf33-80f18b4eae68

        Parameters:
        range - the required range
        Returns:
        the format code

      • streamExistingFormattedValues

        @Deprecated
Stream<IEntry<IRangeAddress,String>> streamExistingFormattedValues(IRangeAddress range)
        Deprecated. current method will be completely removed in future releases, but for the time being it's the only way to get formatted values
        Streams non-empty values with applied format that intersect the given range.

        It means, that all numeric values will be transformed to formatted once.

        For example, if cell contains integer value = 123 with IValue.ValueType.NUMERIC value type and format for this cell is set to $0.00, then this method will return $123.00 instead of 123

        Parameters:
        range - the range at the intersection of which values with applied formatting should be streamed.
        Returns:
        stream of values with applied formatting which intersecting the provided range.
